    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-03-07T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-03-07T12:00:00-05:00" n="546"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/3–751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation to the
                        Torquay Conference</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Torquay</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-07T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 7, 1951—5 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>518. At final session multilateral negots group, memo adopted along lines
                    reported previous tel.<note n="1" xml:id="d546fn1">Apparently the reference is
                        to Torquay telegram 497, March 3, <ref target="#pg_1359">p.
                        1359</ref>.</note> All countries stated intent sign immediately except
                    following: UK dissented. France and Italy stated awaiting signing authority. Can
                    maintained observer role.</p>
                <p>Rpt to London 218, Paris for <gloss target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss> 56, and Rome
                    18.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
